main event: A civilian observed a white-colored object in the sky which blinked like a star and seemed to move in the direction of 285Â° for a total duration of 15 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling toward the southeast, It blinked intermittently and disappeared before reappearing, The observer concluded it was likely Satellite Echo II based on its movement, The observer reported the sighting on 16 Jan 67, The object was described as solid and very bright, potentially brighter than the brightest stars.
sighted object: one bright white object in the sky
witness description: a 33-year-old male graduate student in physics and amateur astronomer
